result.execSummary:
The defendant Jill M Jazdzewski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Homicide by Intoxicated Use of Vehicle, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.09(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[MK] case called at 2:35pm. 
Defendant Jill M Jazdzewski appears via videoconferencing fromTaycheedah Correctional Institution, in custody.  Her counsel, Attorney Thomas Aquino, appears in court.  ADA Monica Hall appears in court for the State of Wisconsin.
A Motion Hearing is scheduled today on the Defendant's 12/12/17 Motion for Postconviction Relief. 
The Court and counsel discuss that Attorney Aquino did not an awareness that he was to provide the certified copy of the Order to Produce to the Jefferson County Sheriff as part of making arrangements for the transport to be done. 
After a review of Statute 967.08 the Court concludes that there cannot be a videoconferencing-appearance on this evidentiary-type of Motion Hearing.  
The Court converts this hearing from a Motion Hearing to a Scheduling Conference, and thereafter the Court finds that the videoconferencing system is sight and sound sufficient. 

The Court observes that [Retired] Judge Wambach is in the courtroom gallery as one of the State's intended motion-hearing witnesses.  The Court informs the parties of the nature of the friendship that the Court has with Judge Wambach. 
After further discussion with counsel, the Court self-disqualifies from this case; there will be a request for an out-of-county judge to be assigned to the case. 
recess 3:05pm.

Defendant Jill M Jazdzewski in court.  ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
Ms. Jazdzewski verifies that the address and date of birth listed on the Criminal Complaint are correct.
Service of Complaint admitted, the charges and maximum penalties are recited; the reading of the factual portion of the Criminal Complaint is waived. 
The Court finds probable cause to exist in the Criminal Complaint. 
Right to counsel given; constructive waiver of counsel warnings given. 
ADA Hall indicates that the State is waiving the Preliminary Hearing time limit.
The Court will schedule a Preliminary Hearing within the twenty day time limit; it will make inquiry related to any waiver of time limits by Ms. Jazdzewski at today's hearing. 

The Court requires a $50,000 Signature Bond, with conditions: 
--Ms. Jazdzewski is to make herself available for drug testing as there may be availability for this testing to be performed; the Court intends to revisit this Bond condition after the DA has the opportunity to confer with WCS in Madison to obtain information on what sample taking and testing can be done
--no possession or consumption of alcohol
--no possession of any medication unless it is specifically prescribed to her
--to take any prescribed medications in the amounts and as directed by the prescription
--not to consume any non-prescribed medications or controlled substances
--no possession of any syringes or hypodermic needles 
--not to drive any motor vehicle under any circumstances
--to apply to the State Public Defender; the Court orders Mr. Jazdzewski to go to the Public Defenders Office in Jefferson today to let them know she seeks for them to represent her, so that arrangements can be made for an application and eligibility determination
--to report to the Jefferson County Sheriff's Department today for booking
